Keep in mind I am in a higher end guild, so these numbers are a little too high for the &quot;average&quot; ranger and warrior. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:perpetua;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=474148">Arch Mage -- Insidious Blood</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skildpade>skildpade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 1:14:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8828.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shield blocking</span><hr size=1> Some people are missing the point.<br>
<br>
In most cases a class that can dual wield benefits little from equipping a shield and sacrificing the damage from the weapon in secondary.<br>
<br>
However, sometimes you might want to equip a shield, either because you can't bash without one or because you really need the stat boost from the shield, usually ac and resists. In this cast I find it excellent that something is done to make it better to equip a shield. It isn't always a matter of DPS, sometimes it is a matter of surviving. Vox raids is an excelent example of this.<br>
 <p>nmee - commander of mudhills<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=407265">nmee's magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tainsumnr>Tain Sumnr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 298<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 2:30:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8828.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shield blocking</span><hr size=1> I saw this as something aimed at people who are tanking mobs, not anyone who can use weapons and equip a shield.  Shields are meant to be defensive, but they do so little that it isn't worth equipping them.  But, if you made them what they should be, defensively, you would start seeing paladins/sk's/warriors drop their 2 handers and go for one hander/shield combos when they have to tank.  I doubt you would see a purely defensive weapon as any real boon to an almost purely offensive class like a ranger...and especially not for a rogue.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arothtb>Aroth TB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 2:51:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8828.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  .</span><hr size=1> Hopefully this will be aimed just a warriors (I know other classes could maybe benifit at it, but to make it work correctly I think it need to be limited - otherwise it'll be so watered down as to be worthless).<br>
<br>
A decent level blocking skill from the shield and perhaps and extra taunt on the bash skill (as tanking is often as much about agro as about defence) could allow warriors to drop the DPS for a better 'tankability'. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailurya@themagicianstower>Ailurya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 3:13:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8828.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shield blocking</span><hr size=1> As much as this sounds like a decent upgrade for Warriors, it also looks like another kick in the teeth for Monks. First they say Monks avoid too much damage on uber mobs so cripple their mitigation at all levels and increase avoidance for other melee classes, now they're talking about making Warriors avoid even more damage too... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=booperbustle>Booperbustle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 3:25:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8828.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shield blocking</span><hr size=1> I can see knight classes and warriors benefiting from this change.  I'm no melee guy (though my first character was a paladin), but exactly what effect did the bash damage rules have on using a shield?  They upgraded the damage to scale with the AC of the shield.  So while you will lose the DPS with that one-handed weapon you're still doing a few 100-200 hits (for high end melees and a decent AC shield) every time you bash.  So if you're not the main tank dual wield or pick up the massive damage two hander in your pack.  Otherwise this would still help mitigate some damage.  <br>
<br>
If they gave casters just a little bit of benefit from this change, that wouldn't be so bad.  The fact is, most casters are putty if they get under heavy fire anyway.  So having even a minute chance of fully blocking a hit here and there wouldn't overbalance things too much.  I'm sure casters would still die even if they were blocking a few of the hits, they'd just have an extra couple of seconds to move away.  <br>
<br>
But when you think about it, warriors really got shafted as a class.  Except on raids, most people would prefer one of the knight classes as a tank (experience groups, etc.).  The idea of the warrior is to take lots of punishment, and do so over any other class.  I think Sony is just trying to balance them out to be a little more desireable across the board.  Right now paladins and SK's are much better tanks in more situations just because they can maintain complete aggro.  I'd think giving warriors some sort of AA ability that gives them a certain percentage increase in the effect of their taunting (or give them a higher cap than knights) would somewhat remedy this situation.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062">Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
